'''Michael Culver''' ([[June 16]], [[1930s#1938|1938]] &ndash; [[February 27]], [[2024]])<ref name="Obituary" /> was a [[Wikipedia:UK|British]] actor who portrayed [[Captain]] [[Lorth Needa]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. His on-screen roles outside the franchise included an appearance in the first episode of the acclaimed crime drama ''Wallander'' alongside fellow Imperial actor [[Malcolm Tierney]], as well as two uncredited appearances in the Bond films ''From Russia With Love'' and ''Thunderball''.

Culver was more prolific as a stage actor, first appearing in several roles with the Dundee Repertory Theatre in 1959 (performing in thirty-five different plays within a two year span) before progressing to the illustrious Old Vic, where many other ''Star Wars'' actors have also appeared; [[John Boyega]], [[James Earl Jones]], [[Indira Varma]], [[Daniel Mays]] and fellow Imperial [[Michael Pennington]] are others who have also worked with the company.

In addition, Culver also narrated several documentaries and has written poetry. He appeared at a number of ''Star Wars'' conventions.

